==English==
===Noun===
'''[[fly]] [[in]] the [[ointment]]'''
#{{idiom}} Something which [[ruins]] or [[spoils]] everything else; a [[nuisance]] or [[problem]]; an [[unpleasant]] or [[disagreeable]] detail.
#:''It's a lovely plan.  The '''fly in the ointment''' is that he will have to sell his house for the money to try it.''

